## ğŸ§  Why This Exploit Works
vsftpd 2.3.4 contains a **hidden malicious backdoor** that opens a remote shell on **port 6200** when a specially crafted username with `:)` is sent.

Metasploit automates the backdoor trigger.

---

## ğŸ”’ Mitigation
- Update vsftpd to the latest version  
- Disable anonymous FTP access  
- Use firewalls to restrict FTP access  

